A First Republic Minister of Aviation, Chief Mbazulike Amaechi, has said it will be improper to sideline the ideals of late Chief Obafemi Awolowo and Dr  Nnamdi Azikiwe in any discourse for the renegotiation of Nigeria. Amaechi reassured his commitment to championing the unity of Nigeria. The nonagenarian said he would never sit back while discussing issues concerning the country, especially its unity. He spoke at weekend during a press conference organised by Global Movement for Igbo Presidency  at his country home in Ukpor, Nnewi South Local Government Area (LGA) of Anambra State.  A First Republic Minister of Aviation, Chief Mbazulike Amaechi, has said it will be improper to sideline the ideals of late Chief Obafemi Awolowo and Dr  Nnamdi Azikiwe in any discourse for the renegotiation of Nigeria. Amaechi reassured his commitment to championing the unity of Nigeria. The nonagenarian said he would never sit back while discussing issues concerning the country, especially its unity. He spoke at weekend during a press conference organised by Global Movement for Igbo Presidency  at his country home in Ukpor, Nnewi South Local Government Area (LGA) of Anambra State. 